sql:
SELECT c.county_name, p.total_population / c.area AS population_density
FROM counties c
JOIN population p ON c.county_id = p.county_id;

SELECT c.county_name, po.poverty_rate
FROM counties c
JOIN poverty po ON c.county_id = po.county_id;

external_knowledge:
In this context, "darkest clouds of economic hardship" metaphorically refers to the counties with the highest number of individuals below the poverty line; "struggling under these conditions" refers to the number of individuals below the poverty line and the poverty rate. ;
The use of a metaphor helps to communicate the severity and impact of poverty on the community. ;
The query aims to highlight the counties that are most affected by poverty within each state to draw attention to areas that need the most support.

sql:
